                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/936</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hartman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 4, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Last Friday Congress passed a resolution repealing the resolution of October last
                    which authorized a commission to adjust differences between Ecuador and
                    Guayaquil and Quito Railway Company. The resolution also declared in full force
                    the resolution of October 1915, which instructed fiscal attorney to bring suit
                    against railway company. Full report by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
